        "comment": {
          "commentType": "FUNCTION",
          "texts": [
            {
              "value": "Mediates the interaction of DNA replication inititator protein DnaA with DNA polymerase subunit beta sliding clamp (dnaN). Stimulates hydrolysis of ATP-DnaA to ADP-DnaA, rendering DnaA inactive for reinititation, a process called regulatory inhibition of DnaA or RIDA"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "annotationType": "ANNOTATION",
        "comment": {
          "commentType": "SIMILARITY",
          "texts": [
            {
              "value": "Belongs to the DnaA family. HdA subfamily"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "annotationType": "ANNOTATION",
        "comment": {
          "commentType": "SUBUNIT",
          "texts": [
            {
              "value": "The active form seems to be an ADP-bound monomer. Forms the RIDA complex (regulatory inactivation of DnaA) of ATP-DnaA, ADP-Hda and the DNA-loaded beta sliding clamp (dnaN)"
            }
          ]
        }
